│ i16 0, 0`, which is always true. This means the `else` block is never entered from the     │
│ loop header, and the `phi` `%p.1` will always receive the value `0` from the               │
│ `%loop.header` predecessor. Therefore, `%p.1` is effectively a loop-invariant constant     │
│ `0`.\n\nConsequently, the `ashr` instruction `%shr.i` is an arithmetic shift of a          │
│ loop-invariant value (`%conv5.i`) by a loop-invariant amount (`0`). The result should be   │
│ loop-invariant. However, SCEV incorrectly classifies `%shr.i` as `Variant`.\n\n### 3. Root │
│ Cause Analysis\n\nThe root of the problem lies in how SCEV analyzes the `phi` node `%p.1`. │
